# World Script Rules

These scripts build and manage game world geometry, POIs, and props.

## Requirements
- All buildings/props must be spawned from POIRegistry data — no hardcoded positions
- Every spawned node must have a unique `name` matching its `poi_id` or prop type
- Collision layers: 1 = world geometry, 2 = player, 4 = NPCs, 8 = interaction zones
- Area3D interaction zones must connect `body_entered`/`body_exited` with the POI id bound
- Street props (lights, benches, bins) go under the `Buildings` node
- Materials: set `roughness` >= 0.85 for the brutalist aesthetic
- Parks use flat geometry (height 0.15), not full building boxes
- Label3D signs: billboard mode enabled, pixel_size 0.01, outline_size 8
